HEADWORD: Salina period
<hw>Sa*li"na pe"ri*od</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[So called from
<ets>Salina</ets>, a town in New York.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>The period in which the American Upper Silurian system, containing
the brine-producing rocks of central New York, was formed. See the
<xex>Chart</xex> of <er>Geology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Salination</ent>⟦br⟧
